carry generic parameter lists at the declaration site (associated types serve
that role and are emitted as requirements inside the body). The inheritance
clause refers exclusively to other protocols; the HIR uses the field name
'inherited_protocols' rather than the class-style 'inheritance' to make this
explicit. Modifiers are omitted because no source-level modifiers apply to
protocols other than the access keyword already handled.
